      • horizSplit

        public GroupReportData horizSplit(CellColumn z)
        Description copied from class: ReportData
        recursively split this instance into subinstances. The leaves should generate new leaves, each one of them equaling a given value, governed by the respective leaf's Behaviour
        Specified by:
        horizSplit in class ReportData
        Returns:

      • horizSplit

        public GroupReportData horizSplit(ColumnContents dataColumn,
                                  ColumnContents wholeColumn,
                                  Behaviour<?> behaviour,
                                  NiReportColumn<?> schemaColumn,
                                  boolean enqueueAcceptors)
        Horizontally splits this instance by a given CellColumn. Every entityId in the given splitter column will create a subreport. Each and every CellColumn in this instance will be filtered repeatedly, according to Behaviour.horizSplit(ColumnContents, Map, Set, Map, boolean, boolean). Every nonempty subreport is kept and output as a child ColumnReportData of the generated GroupReportData. What constitutes a "nonempty subreport" is subject to
          >:
          • spec: ReportSpecification.isDisplayEmptyFundingRows()
          • type of hierarchy-generator column: NiReportsSchema.isTransactionLevelHierarchy(NiReportColumn, NiReportsEngine)
        Parameters:
        dataColumn - the column driving the hierarchy
        wholeColumn - the full contents, as fetched, of the column driving the hierarchy
        behaviour - the behaviour of the driving column
        schemaColumn - the schema column of the driving column
        enqueueAcceptors - whether to enqueue the acceptors, for each individual cell. Used for the "filtering as collapsed hierachies" functionality
        Returns:
